# 7. 『お母さん』

Kanade: Let's see... I'm supposed to meet her somewhere around here...
Kanade: (I need to say everything I can. For Mafuyu's sake...)
Kanade: (I'm sure she cares about Mafuyu very much...)
Kanade: (So I'm hoping that if I can explain to her just how much Mafuyu is suffering over the prospect of not being able to work on music anymore is taking a significant mental toll on her...)
Kanade: (Which is why I'm not going to tell any lies or half-truths. I'll tell her what's going on and try to find the best solution I can.)
Kanade: Oh, that lady...
Kanade: (She looks just like Mafuyu. Is she...?)
Mafuyu's Mother: Are you K...?
Kanade: Y-Yes, my name is Kanade Yoisaki. It's been a pleasure working with Mafuyu.
Kanade: I'm looking forward to talking to you today.
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. I'm Yuki's mother. Thank you for agreeing to meet with me today, Ms. Yoisaki.
Mafuyu's Mother: I apologize for what happened the other day. I may've sounded rather cold due to my not being used to chatting on a computer.
Kanade: No, that didn't bother me... I'm also not very used to chatting online.
Kanade: (Thank goodness... She seems like a nice person...)
Mafuyu's Mother: Also, Ms. Yoisaki, you know Mafuyu's real name...?
Kanade: Yes, we've met offline...I mean, in real life a few times...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, I see...
Mafuyu's Mother: Anyway, we have much to discuss today. Shall we find a place where we can sit and talk?
Kanade: O-Of course...
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. There's no need to feel so anxious. You have my word that it's a nice place.
Mafuyu's Mother: Still, it is a fairly fancy establishment. I also felt a little nervous when I first came here.
Mafuyu's Mother: But don't worry, I'm sure you'll get used to it.
Kanade: A-Are you sure...?
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes. So, let's try to have a relaxing time.
Mafuyu's Mother: We actually always come here as a family to celebrate Mafuyu's various achievements.
Kanade: ...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, my apologies. I'm just so excited about having the opportunity to speak with one of Mafuyu's friends that I can't seem to contain my excitement.
Mafuyu's Mother: Anyway, how does a cake and a drink sound...? I'd like you to try it since the ones they bake here are very good.
Kanade: Yes, sure... Thank you very much.
Mafuyu's Mother: Now, about why we're here...
Mafuyu's Mother: When did you first meet Mafuyu?
Kanade: When...?
Kanade: Um... I'd say around two years ago.
Mafuyu's Mother: I see... What sorts of things do you usually do with her?
Kanade: We're in a music group that produces songs. Mafuyu's in charge of writing lyrics for us...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, that. I'm sorry. I took the liberty of looking at some of her lyrics...
Mafuyu's Mother: And your songs are nice. Making music with friends seems like such a wonderful hobby.
Kanade: Th-Thank you very much...
Mafuyu's Mother: Hehe. I listen to classical music quite a lot, but I never thought about creating my own songs. I was so surprised when I first found out that Mafuyu is doing just that...
Mafuyu's Mother: Isn't it hard to produce the songs that you do?
Kanade: Oh, um... It really isn't. But it can be when I don't have any ideas...
Kanade: But Mafuyu and the others in our group have helped me quite a lot with that.
Mafuyu's Mother: I see. Hehe. I'm glad to hear that she's been able to help.
Mafuyu's Mother: But you must all be busy preparing for your own entrance exams. You're all around the same age as Mafuyu, no?
Mafuyu's Mother: I'm sure it isn't easy for you to write songs while also going to school, Ms. Yoisaki.
Kanade: (Her tone changed...)
Kanade: Oh, um... Not all of us are studying for exams...
Kanade: That includes myself... I'm not actually studying for any...
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, is that so...
Mafuyu's Mother: Then, you don't plan on pursuing higher education...?
Kanade: No, not at the moment... Music is more important to me than exams right now...
Mafuyu's Mother: I see...
Mafuyu's Mother: I admire the fact that you have something you're so passionate about...
Kanade: (She's taking it much better than I was expecting...)
Kanade: (But...)
Kanade: (I'm getting shivers down my spine...)
Mafuyu's Mother: Also, I mentioned this when we chatted before... But, no different from you, Mafuyu's pursuing a big dream.
Mafuyu's Mother: To become a doctor. Isn't it wonderful?
Kanade: A doctor...?
Kanade: (That's Mafuyu's dream...? I had no idea... But...)
Kanade: (Something doesn't seem right here...)
Mafuyu: <I just don't understand. I live my life every day, but nothing gives me pleasure or joy.>
Mafuyu: <Everything feels detached or impersonal.>
Mafuyu: <Yet I can sense that something vital is missing.>
Mafuyu: <How do I even put this into words?>
Kanade: (In the beginning, Mafuyu wasn't sure what she wanted to do with herself...)
Kanade: (So much so that she wanted to disappear completely...)
Kanade: (If it's true that Mafuyu does want to become a doctor more than anything else, then...)
Mafuyu: I told her no...! I said that I didn't want to give up music!
Mafuyu: But...! She didn't care...
Mafuyu: What else can I do at this point...?!
Kanade: (No, she wouldn't have said that.)
Kanade: (This person in front of me is convinced that she cares about Mafuyu... However...)
Mafuyu's Mother: So, I'd like to ask you once more today regarding Mafuyu's dream in life...
Mafuyu's Mother: For her sake, at least until she's finished taking her entrance exams, please refrain from contacting her...
Kanade: Yes, I understand that she needs to study...
Kanade: But I also feel that Mafuyu needs music right now...
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, I agree that it's important to take breaks from time to time.
Kanade: Yes, but... That's not what I meant...
Kanade: Mafuyu told me herself that she doesn't want to give up music.
Kanade: Which is why I'd like for you to allow her to keep working with us. It only has to be when she has some free time on her hands.
Kanade: Because in her current state...
Mafuyu's Mother: Yes, of course...
Kanade: Huh...?
Mafuyu's Mother: Didn't I just say that it's important to take breaks?
Mafuyu's Mother: Also, I don't plan on forcing her to give up music entirely until she's done taking her exams...
Kanade: Oh... I see...
Kanade: (So, she's not completely against Mafuyu making music with us...?)
Kanade: (Then, I might actually be able to get somewhere with her. My assumptions about her may've been misplaced...)
Mafuyu's Mother: But I would like for her to stop working with this group of yours...
Kanade: What...?
Mafuyu's Mother: I don't know much about it, but you have deadlines and such to meet, yes...?
Mafuyu's Mother: And writing lyrics sounds very time-consuming... If she were able to work at her own pace, then she'd be able to participate without it taking away from her studies...
Mafuyu's Mother: Also, Mafuyu's so kind that she may be having trouble saying that she'd rather be studying instead of doing anything music-related...
Kanade: B-But that won't work for her...
Kanade: I believe that Mafuyu wants and needs to make music with us... Together!
Mafuyu's Mother: Oh, what makes you say that...?
Kanade: I, um...
Kanade: (How do I tell her that I'm trying to save her...?)
Mafuyu's Mother: Please don't take this personally...
Mafuyu's Mother: I understand that not being able to see or talk to Mafuyu anymore is going to be difficult after working with her for these past two years...
Mafuyu's Mother: But I'd like to take this opportunity to say...
Mafuyu's Mother: Your little music group... There is no room in her life for such a thing.
Kanade: ...!
Mafuyu's Mother: So, if you truly do care about Mafuyu, you'll ask her to leave your group.
Mafuyu's Mother: I'm sure she'll understand if she hears it coming from your mouth.
Kanade: (No...)
Kanade: (Something's definitely wrong here...!)
Kanade: (She seems to care about Mafuyu... I can tell that she spends a lot of time thinking about her.)
Kanade: (But... Something's wrong. This doesn't feel right...)
Kanade: (I'm used to a different kind of warmth. She just feels...)
